% A2 — README's escape list omits `^`
%
% README.md:597 (Escape rules section) lists four characters that are
% auto-escaped in prose: `_ & % ~`.
%
% Code at scholatex.lua:299-303 actually auto-escapes FIVE characters:
% `_ & % ^ ~`. The standalone manual (scholatex.tex:361) is correct.
%
% This MWE just demonstrates that `^` in prose is automatically escaped
% to a literal `^` character in the PDF (rather than raising a "missing $
% inserted" error from LaTeX as it would in raw LaTeX). The bug is purely
% README:597; this MWE confirms the code behavior so the issue can quote
% the actual rule.
\documentclass[lang=en]{scholatex}
\begin{document}

The caret character ^ should appear literally in this paragraph.

So should 100 ^ 2 in the math-free context (as part of the sentence).

\end{document}
